  "slug": "spicy-braised-chicken",
  "source": "This recipe is inspired by the Netflix’s Korean fried chicken rhapsody show and the spicy braised chicken recipe from Aaron Huh’s book “Simply Korean: Easy recipes for Korean favorites that anyone can make”.",
  "steps": [
    {
      "name": "",
      "steps": [
        {
          "text": "Prepare the vegetables.<br>\n**Potatoes and carrots:** peel, and cut into large chunks. **Tomatoes:** remove cores, and cut into medium dice. **Onion:** peel, halve, and cut into 1/2 cm slices. **Jalapeño:** halve lengthwise, remove the seeds, and thinly slice.<br>\n**Garlic:** peel.",
          "pause": false
        },
        {
          "text": "Rinse the chicken in cold water. Cut it into pieces: wings, drumsticks, thighs, then split the breast into several smaller parts.",
          "pause": false
        },
        {
          "text": "Cover the bottom of the Dutch oven with olive oil, and heat it on medium-high heat.",
          "pause": false
        },
        {
          "text": "Brown the chicken on all sides.",
          "pause": false
        },
        {
          "text": "While the chicken is browning, prepare the seasoning paste.",
          "pause": false
        },
        {
          "text": "Mix in a blender garlic, <Ingredient name=\"chile de árbol\"  />, <Ingredient name=\"chile\" modifier=\"guajillo\" />, <Ingredient name=\"soy sauce\"  />, <Ingredient name=\"oyster sauce\"  />, <Ingredient name=\"maple syrup\"  /> or 2 tablespoons of coconut sugar, and 1/2 cup of water.",
          "pause": false
        },
        {
          "text": "Pour the seasoning paste into the Dutch oven, add salt, and cook covered on medium-low heat for about 20 minutes.",
          "pause": false
        },
        {
          "text": "Add potatoes, carrots, tomatoes, onions, jalapeño, hot water (it should almost cover the food), increase the heat to medium-high, and bring to a boil.",
          "pause": false
        },
        {
          "text": "Reduce the heat to medium, and simmer covered, stirring occasionally, for about 15 minutes, until all the vegetables are ready.",
          "pause": false
        }
      ]
    }
  ],
